cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks and specifically focuses on developing attention mechanisms for uncertainty detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The development of novel architectures for attention mechanisms involves experimentation and comparison, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). The use of external resources and sequence information also suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of linguistic features, which could potentially fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
